Method Detail

invoke

public A invoke(A aggregate,
                P value)
Returns the result of the aggregation-function passed in the constructor as an object of the aggregate type. The function is invoked with the last aggregation value (the last status of the aggregation) and the next value that should be considered by the aggregation-function.

Overrides:
invoke in class DecoratorAggregationFunction<P,A>
Parameters:
aggregate - the last aggregate returned by the function. When it is set to null the aggregation-function is initialized, i.e., it acts as it is called the very first time.
value - the next value that should be considered by the aggregation-function.
Returns:
the new aggregate.
